---
import '../../styles/global.css';

const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="description" content="Support for Tabi Travel App" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Support - Tabi</title>
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-900 font-mono">
  <div class="min-h-screen max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-12">
      <nav class="mb-8">
        <a href="/projects/tabi" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm">← Back to Tabi</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">Support - Tabi</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="space-y-8">      
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Getting Started</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: How do I set up Tabi?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: Simply download the app and grant location permissions when prompted. Tabi will automatically start tracking your travels in the background. No account creation or additional setup required.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: Why isn't Tabi tracking my location?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: Check that you've granted "Always" location permission in iOS Settings > Privacy & Security > Location Services > Tabi. The app needs background location access to track your travels automatically.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Privacy & Data</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: Where is my location data stored?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: All your travel data stays on your device. We never upload your location information to any servers. Only you have access to your travel history.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: Can you see my location data?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: No. Since all data is stored locally on your device, we have no access to your location information or travel patterns.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: Does Tabi use any internet connection?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: Only to convert coordinates into city/country names using Apple's geocoding service. Your raw location coordinates are never sent to our servers.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Features & Usage</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: How often does Tabi track my location?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: Tabi tracks your location every few hours to balance accuracy with battery life. The exact interval may vary based on your movement and device settings.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: Will Tabi drain my battery?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: Tabi is optimized for minimal battery usage. It uses efficient background location tracking that shouldn't noticeably impact your battery life.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: How do I export my travel data?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: Go to Settings > Export Data within the app. You can export your travel history in multiple formats for tax records, visa applications, or personal backup.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Q: What happens if I delete the app?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  A: All your travel data will be permanently deleted since it's stored only on your device. Make sure to export your data first if you want to keep it.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Need Help?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              If you can't find the answer to your question in our FAQ, we're here to help:
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Email:</strong> help@meiwin.helpscoutapp.com
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">App Store Reviews</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Love Tabi? Please consider leaving a review on the App Store. It helps other travelers discover our privacy-focused travel tracking.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <p class="text-center text-gray-400 mt-4">
        © {currentYear} /meiwin/. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>